studyMetadata.title: Stage 1 (COVID-19)
studyMetadata.description: A study challenging participants to review linecharts.

uiConfig.studyEndMsg: **Thank you for completing the study. You may click this link and return to Prolific**: [Add your link](Add your link)

covid.instruction: Imagine you work for your country’s public health department. Your colleague claimed that the highlighted country’s COVID-19 response was one of the most effective. The visualization below depicts the total infections to date. Please review the chart and answer the questions below.

response.prompt: Imagine your job is to select a public health policymaker from another country to advise you on COVID-19 response. Based on the visualization above, how likely are you to choose a policymaker from the highlighted country?
How well did the country manage COVID-19 compared to all other countries? Drag the slider to answer (1 means 'worst' and 100 means 'best.')
Do you feel that the visualization provided appropriate context to make an informed decision about adopting a COVID-19 policy?

covid-metadata.instruction: Below are four different visualizations (A–D) of COVID-19 data for Norway. Please review each chart and select the one you think is the most useful comparison for Norway.

response.prompt: Which visualization (A, B, C, or D) do you think depicts the best comparison for Norway's performance?
Explain your reasoning for selecting this chart.
Do you consent to the study and wish to continue?
How familiar are you with COVID-19 pandemic response, policies, and their impacts?
How comfortable do you feel interpreting numbers, percentages, and basic statistics?
How confident are you in your ability to accurately interpret charts, graphs, and other visualizations?
